Vice President Joe Biden announced Kareem Dale as the Special Assistant to the President for Disability Policy. This is the first time a president has had a special assistant focused exclusively on disability policy. Dale, who is partially blind, will have direct access to the president and will coordinate efforts to ensure that people with disabilities have equal opportunities. He previously served as the National Disability Director for the Obama for America campaign and was involved in various committees related to arts and disability policy. Dale graduated from the University of Illinois at Urbana-Champaign with a Bachelor's degree in Advertising and received his JD/MBA from the same university.